2016-07-07 00:49file< p > DAENERYS < / p >
2016-07-07 00:49fileDaenerys Targaryen awaited him upon the ebon bench that she had made her throne.
2016-07-07 00:49file< p > "Your Grace,” said Ser Barristan Selmy, the Lord Commander of her Queensguard, "there is no need for you to see this ."
2016-07-07 00:49fileDany clutched her lion pelt to her chest.
2016-07-07 00:49fileShe had been dreaming of a house with a red door when Missandei woke her.
2016-07-07 00:49file< p > Dany paid no heed.
2016-07-07 00:49fileKhal Drogo had given them to her, who was her sun-and-stars.
2016-07-07 00:49fileDrogo had given her the pelt too, the head and hide of a < emphasis > hrakkar, < / emphasis > the white lion of the Dothraki sea.
2016-07-07 00:49fileIt was too big for her and had a musty smell, but it made her feel as if Drogo were still near her.
2016-07-07 00:49file< p > Grey Worm appeared atop the steps first, a torch in hand.
2016-07-07 00:49fileSer Barristan pulled back the blood-stained shroud.
2016-07-07 00:49fileGrey Worm lowered the torch, so she might see.
2016-07-07 00:49file< p > "Your Grace,” Ser Barristan said, "there was a harpy drawn on the bricks in the alley where he was found.
2016-07-07 00:49fileDaenerys knew the way of it by now.
2016-07-07 00:49file"Grey Worm, why was this man alone?
2016-07-07 00:49file< p > "Even those who lack a man’s parts may still have a man’s heart, Your Grace,” said Grey Worm.
2016-07-07 00:49file< p > "Six or more,” said Ser Barristan.
2016-07-07 00:49file< p > Dany said a silent prayer that somewhere one of them was dying even now, clutching at his belly and writhing in pain.
2016-07-07 00:49file< p > "Gracious queen,” said Grey Worm, "his killers had forced the genitals of a goat down the throat of your servant Stalwart Shield.
2016-07-07 00:49file< / emphasis > "The Sons grow bolder,” Dany observed.
